description._content: Description: A regatta with locally-constructed craft on an artificial lake at Tembi. The power-house supplying electricity to the Oil-Fields is seen on the right. Location: Tembi, Persia Description: Aquatic sports with locally-built craft on the artificial lake near the Tembi Pumping Station. Location: Tembi, Persia Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/714 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown. We have attempted to provide place information for the images automatically but our software may not have found the correct location.
